WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:25.000
HeartAnalysis is an educational Flutter and Flask prototype. The heuristic is unvalidated and is not a medical risk estimate, diagnosis, prognosis, or treatment recommendation.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:55.000
The built-in profile is deterministic and synthetic. The grouped form preserves the Material design while making the intended path immediate and repeatable.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Pydantic validates the request. Compatibility fields remain, while score metadata states that the result is uncalibrated and is not a medical probability.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:55.000
The scorecard explains configured factor contributions. These values explain program behavior; they do not demonstrate causality or clinical validity.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:02:18.000
Rules mode supplies deterministic, network-free educational guidance. External model adapters exist but are not release-verified.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:48.000
The What-If screen changes one synthetic input and compares deterministic score movement. It is not an individual outcome prediction.

00:02:48.000 --> 00:03:12.000
History is enabled only for this isolated local synthetic demo. Persistence is off by default because the API has no user authentication or tenant isolation.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:38.000
The assistant uses the same rules boundary and always includes non-medical guidance. It cannot diagnose or replace emergency care.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:04:17.000
The release is verified by API and Flutter tests, dependency audits, a production build, Chromium workflow checks, and inspected video frames. No clinical or public-production claim is made.
